text: The 2010 Tasmanian state election was held on 20 March 2010 to elect all 25 members of the Tasmanian House of Assembly. It was conducted by the Tasmanian Electoral Commission (TEC). The incumbent Labor government, led by Premier David Bartlett, won a fourth term in government, after forming a minority government with the Greens. They were opposed by the Liberal Party, led by Will Hodgman. ==References== Category:2010 elections in Australia Category:Elections in Tasmania Category:2010s in Tasmania
title: 2010 Tasmanian state election
